2.00	L'amourha	L'amourha	L'amourha is the third album of Sielun Veljet. It was their breakthrough album, gaining much of its success from the hit single "Peltirumpu". It is the only Sielun Veljet album to come close to the sales figures of Ismo Alanko's previous group, Hassisen Kone, and remains one of Alanko's most popular works. The album was named the fourth greatest Finnish rock album by Soundi magazine in 2005.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/53/Lamourha_cover.jpg/220px-Lamourha_cover.jpg
